<h3><t>Sponsorship proposal</t></h3>

<div class="contentarea">
<h4>Sponsor Us</h4>

<p>
<strong>Who are we?</strong>
</p>

<p>
The Netherlands Perl Workshop (NLPW) is a day of presentations and encounters by and for Perl users with interesting content for new and experienced users of the Perl programming language. Take place diverse location in the Netherlands once a year with 40-70 participants. This year we are at Arnhem.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Sponsorship Proposal</strong>
</p>

<p>
One of the key principles behind NLPW is the minimal price for the attendees. The role of sponsors is so important because NLPW is not commercial events. To make this awesome conference  happen, we need money. If you want to give something back to the Perl community and support us, we would be happy to welcome you as a sponsor.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Sponsorship Levels</strong>
</p>

<p>
Sponsorship can take many forms, such as:
</p>
<ul>
<li> Direct financial donations </li>
<li> Sponsorship of specific items  </li>
<li> Help with a conference expense (we have many, so contact us for details) </li>
</ul>

<p>
We offer four sponsorship levels (details see below):
</p>
<ul>
<li> Sponsors (min.  400€) </li>
<li> Bronze Sponsors (min. 800€) </li>
<li> Silver Sponsors (min. 1300 €) </li>
<li> Gold Sponsors (min. 2000 €)</li>
</ul>

<p>
If you want to discuss some details, or propose something different, you can write us an email: organisatie@perlworkshop.nl
Please contact the organizers for opportunities that are not listed here. For example, we may provide a special proposal for the sponsor willing to cover one of our guest speakers travel expenses or the attendees dinner(BBQ).
The following list name the items that each sponsorship level offers.
</p>

<p>
<h5>Gold Sponsors</h5>
</p>
<ul>
<li> 3 free tickets for the conference </li>
<li> A table at the central place</li>
<li> 3 technical talk slot</li>
<li> Goodies distributed at the registration desk </li>
<li> Logotype on the website </li>
<li> A link on the website</li>
<li> Room named after sponsor</li>
<li> Explicitly mentioned and thanked at beginning and end of the conference</li>
<li> Description on the website (up to 500 characters) </li>
</ul>

<p>
<h5>Silver Sponsors</h5>
</p>
<ul>
<li> 2 free tickets for the conference </li>
<li> A table at the central place</li>
<li> 2 technical talk slot</li>
<li> Goodies distributed at the registration desk</li>
<li> Logotype on the website </li>
<li> A link on the website </li>
<li> Room named after sponsor</li>
<li> Explicitly mentioned and thanked at beginning and end of the conference</li>
<li> Description on the website (up to 200 characters) </li>
</ul>

<p>
<h5>Bronze Sponsors</h5>
</p>
<ul>
<li> 1 free ticket for the conference </li>
<li> Goodies distributed at the registration desk</li>
<li> Logotype on the website </li>
<li> A link on the website </li>
<li> Explicitly mentioned and thanked at beginning and end of the conference</li>
<li> Description on the website (up to 100 characters) </li>
</ul>

<p>
<h5>Sponsors</h5>
</p>
<ul>
<li> Logotype on the website </li>
<li> A link on the website </li>
</ul>

<p>
Despite these four levels, it may not be suitable for your needs. Thus, we may provide a special proposal for the sponsor willing to cover one of our guest speakers travel expenses, the attendees dinner(BBQ), For example, you might sponsor one of the following:
</p>
<ul>
<li> BBQ- dinner: est. 1000€ </li>
<li> Badges, paperwork and other goodies: est. 1200€ </li>
<li> Hackathlon on Sunday: est. 500€</li>
<li> Hoodies: est. 1600€</li>
<li> T-shirts: est. 1200€ </li>
</ul>

<p>
In any case, if no one of those levels fit your needs, please, feel free to contact the organizers for opportunities that are not listed here. Lets discuss the details, your needs, your offer… Propose something different writing us an email: organisatie@perlworkshop.nl.
</p>

<p>
<strong>The Organizers</strong>
</p>

<p>
The organization team members are currently from Amsterdam.pm, Arnhem.pm and DenHaag.pm.
Please address any questions and comments related to the conference and sponsorship to the Organizing Committee at organisatie@perlworkshop.nl
</p>

